  "lessons": [
    {
      "key": "Pre-Assessment",
      "name": "Pre-Assessment",
      "absolute_position": 1,
      "lockable": true,
      "has_lesson_plan": false,
      "relative_position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "assessment": true,
        "preparation": "- Unlock the assessment questions as indicated on the Unlocking Assessments resource"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "lesson.key": "Pre-Assessment",
        "lesson_group.key": "lessonGroup-2",
        "script.name": "aif6-v2-2025"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "Lesson 1: Introduction to Data Science",
      "name": "Lesson 1: Introduction to Data Science",
      "absolute_position": 2,
      "lockable": false,
      "has_lesson_plan": true,
      "relative_position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "overview": "<i class=\"fa-solid fa-user-graduate\"></i> ***Career Journeys***\n\n**What is data science, and how can it be used?**\n\nThis is a survey lesson introducing students to all sorts of things data science can do. Students start with a pre-assessment asking them to find data in an image of a class pizza party, to introduce the concept of data and data science. Students then learn about a specific data scientist, who they will represent in conversations with their classmates. As they discuss with their classmates, they will learn about the other data scientists.",
        "preparation": "* Provide copies of the Unit 1 Guided Notes for each student\n* Print copies of the Data Scientist Bingo Card (one for each student)\n* Print copies of the Data Scientists Tents (one for each student)\n* Gather several sticky notes (2-3 for each student)",
        "student_overview": "**What is data science, and how can it be used?**\n\nBecome an expert in a data scientist, what they do and their path to getting there. Then, represent that data scientist for the rest of the class, and learn about other data scientists."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "lesson.key": "Lesson 1: Introduction to Data Science",
        "lesson_group.key": "lessonGroup-3",
        "script.name": "aif6-v2-2025"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "Lesson 2: Making Sense of Data",
      "name": "Lesson 2: Making Sense of Data",
      "absolute_position": 3,
      "lockable": false,
      "has_lesson_plan": true,
      "relative_position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "overview": "**What do the different values in a spreadsheet represent?**\n\nStudents work with data in a spreadsheet before using a routine called Three Reads to familiarize themselves with a dataset about pizza choices. Then students will use the dataset to try and answer some questions that will be helpful in planning a school event.",
        "preparation": "* Refer to the Guide to Anchor Charts to set up a Spreadsheet Anchor Chart\n* Print copies of the Answering a Data Question activity guide (one for each student)",
        "student_overview": "**What do the different values in a spreadsheet represent?**\n\nYou’ll work with a dataset in a spreadsheet and use it to help start planning a school event."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "lesson.key": "Lesson 2: Making Sense of Data",
        "lesson_group.key": "lessonGroup-3",
        "script.name": "aif6-v2-2025"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "Lesson 3: Ethical Data Collection",
      "name": "Lesson 3: Ethical Data Collection",
      "absolute_position": 4,
      "lockable": false,
      "has_lesson_plan": true,
      "relative_position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "overview": "**Where does data come from?**\n\nIn this lesson, students will have the opportunity to learn about multiple aspects of data collection. They will collect and store classroom data, explore ethical considerations that must be made when choosing the types of data that are collected, and delve into the different ways that data might be collected.",
        "preparation": "* Print copies of the Data Collection Methods datasets (one set for each pair of students)\n* **(Optional)** Cut out the Data Collection Methods datasets and place in baggies\n* Gather several sticky notes (3-4 for each pair of students)",
        "student_overview": "**Where does data come from?**\n\nIn this lesson, you will be examining the how and why of data collection. You will learn about the various ways that data might be collected and stored, as well as explore the important ethical considerations that accompany any collection of data."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "lesson.key": "Lesson 3: Ethical Data Collection",
        "lesson_group.key": "lessonGroup-3",
        "script.name": "aif6-v2-2025"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "Lesson 4: Data Rights",
      "name": "Lesson 4: Data Rights",
      "absolute_position": 5,
      "lockable": false,
      "has_lesson_plan": true,
      "relative_position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "overview": "**What are my rights when it comes to data?**\n\nIn this lesson, students will examine and evaluate fundamental data rights. By examining a variety of different stakeholders' points of view, students will engage in data rights conversations. They will attempt to empathize with different positions in order to strengthen their understanding of the nuance inherent in data rights discussions.",
        "preparation": "* Print copies of the Privacy Policy Statements (one statement for each student)\n* Cut out the Privacy Policy Statements so each student receives one statement\n* Print copies of the Data Rights Exploration activity guide (one for each student)",
        "student_overview": "**What are my rights when it comes to data?**\n\nIn this lesson, you will be examining data rights – a set of rules that make sure a person's information is used safely and fairly. You will explore several different stakeholder, each of which have different viewpoints when it comes to data rights."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "lesson.key": "Lesson 4: Data Rights",
        "lesson_group.key": "lessonGroup-3",
        "script.name": "aif6-v2-2025"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "Lesson 5: Effective Data Questions",
      "name": "Lesson 5: Effective Data Questions",
      "absolute_position": 6,
      "lockable": false,
      "has_lesson_plan": true,
      "relative_position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "overview": "**How can we determine if a question is effective for analyzing a given dataset?**\n\nIn this lesson, students will explore how to derive insightful and meaningful questions from a provided dataset, utilizing established criteria to evaluate and refine their inquiries. Starting with an engaging data talk where students guess potential questions behind displayed visualizations, the lesson progresses through a systematic approach to understanding and applying key characteristics of effective questions. Students will engage in hands-on activities to rank, refine, and ultimately formulate their own data-driven questions, with an emphasis on relevance, clarity, measurability, and ethical considerations.",
        "preparation": "* Print copies of the Possible Questions activity guide (one for each student)\n* Print copies of the Guided Notes - Criteria for Creating Effective Questions activity guide (one for each student)",
        "student_overview": "**How can we determine if a question is effective for analyzing a given dataset?**\n\nIn this lesson,  you’ll discover how to craft powerful questions that let you explore datasets like a data scientist. We’ll kick things off by guessing the questions behind intriguing data visuals. Then, you’ll learn about the key criteria that make a question really effective, helping you learn exactly what to consider when you dive into any dataset."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "lesson.key": "Lesson 5: Effective Data Questions",
        "lesson_group.key": "lessonGroup-3",
        "script.name": "aif6-v2-2025"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "Lesson 6: Data Storytelling",
      "name": "Lesson 6: Data Storytelling",
      "absolute_position": 7,
      "lockable": false,
      "has_lesson_plan": true,
      "relative_position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "overview": "**How can we use data to tell meaningful and engaging stories?**\n\nIn this lesson, students will explore both expository and persuasive data stories and learn some of the properties that are unique to each. They will explore several real-life examples of data stories in order to learn the traits that make telling a data story engaging and insightful.",
        "preparation": "* Print copies of the Data Storytelling activity guide (one for each student)",
        "student_overview": "**How can we use data to tell meaningful and engaging stories?**\n\nIn this lesson, you will explore two different ways to tell data stories that are sure to engage an audience to make your data more presentable, interesting, and engaging. You will explore Spotify’s Year Wrapped feature to learn about expository data stories, and will explore how an author takes that stance that LeBron James is the G.O.A.T. to learn about persuasive data stories."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "lesson.key": "Lesson 6: Data Storytelling",
        "lesson_group.key": "lessonGroup-3",
        "script.name": "aif6-v2-2025"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "Lesson 7: Introduction to Data Visualization",
      "name": "Lesson 7: Introduction to Data Visualization",
      "absolute_position": 8,
      "lockable": false,
      "has_lesson_plan": true,
      "relative_position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "overview": "**How do we create data visualizations that help us better understand the data?**\n\nIn this lesson, students create charts in a spreadsheet editor to practice building basic data visualizations – bar charts and pie charts. As they practice building each sort of data visualization, they also discuss when and where each type of visualization might be useful. Finally, they will learn how to filter their data in a spreadsheet.",
        "student_overview": "**How do we create data visualizations that help us better understand the data?**\n\nIn this lesson, you'll get to dive into the world of data visualizations, making several of your own in a spreadsheet editor."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "lesson.key": "Lesson 7: Introduction to Data Visualization",
        "lesson_group.key": "lessonGroup-3",
        "script.name": "aif6-v2-2025"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "Lesson 8: Data Cleaning and Analysis Techniques",
      "name": "Lesson 8: Data Cleaning and Analysis Techniques",
      "absolute_position": 9,
      "lockable": false,
      "has_lesson_plan": true,
      "relative_position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "overview": "**What do data scientists need to do to make data usable?**\n\nIn this lesson, students look at how raw data can be in a format that prevents useful insights from being drawn. Students practice making the decisions that go into cleaning data and debrief with each other over the challenging parts of that process. The lesson concludes with a discussion about the tradeoffs inherent in these decisions since they can introduce bias and inaccuracy into a dataset.",
        "preparation": "* Make an empty anchor chart for synthesizing the discussion on cleaning data",
        "student_overview": "**What do data scientists need to do to make data usable?**\n\nWork with data that comes in a raw format that needs to be cleaned in order to be useful."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "lesson.key": "Lesson 8: Data Cleaning and Analysis Techniques",
        "lesson_group.key": "lessonGroup-3",
        "script.name": "aif6-v2-2025"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "Lesson 9: Data Interpretation",
      "name": "Lesson 9: Data Interpretation",
      "absolute_position": 10,
      "lockable": false,
      "has_lesson_plan": true,
      "relative_position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "overview": "**How do the visualizations data scientists choose impact our interpretation of data?**\n\nThis lesson delves into how various data visualizations can shape our understanding of the same topic, emphasizing identifying trends, patterns, and outliers. Students will analyze individual datasets and discuss insights from different perspectives. ",
        "preparation": "* Print out copies of the activity guide for each dataset",
        "student_overview": "**How do the visualizations data scientists choose impact our interpretation of data?**\n\nIn this lesson, you'll explore how different visualizations influence our understanding of the same data. Through individual analysis and group collaboration, you'll learn to identify trends, patterns, outliers, and the impact of how data is presented."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "lesson.key": "Lesson 9: Data Interpretation",
        "lesson_group.key": "lessonGroup-3",
        "script.name": "aif6-v2-2025"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "Lesson 10: More Visualization Techniques",
      "name": "Lesson 10: More Visualization Techniques",
      "absolute_position": 11,
      "lockable": false,
      "has_lesson_plan": true,
      "relative_position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "overview": "**How can we gain deeper insights into our data?**\n\nIn this lesson, students will deepen their understanding of data visualization by using additional features available in spreadsheets to analyze various datasets. They learn to use formulas and other visualization tools to interpret data through different lenses and discuss ethical considerations such as bias and privacy. The lesson aims to enhance their skills in technical data handling and critical thinking about the impacts of data analysis.",
        "student_overview": "**How can we gain deeper insights into our data?**\n\nIn this lesson,  you'll dive into advanced data visualization techniques with a spreadsheet. You'll learn how to reveal deeper insights from data and discuss the importance of using these tools responsibly. Get ready to uncover the hidden stories data can tell!"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "lesson.key": "Lesson 10: More Visualization Techniques",
        "lesson_group.key": "lessonGroup-3",
        "script.name": "aif6-v2-2025"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "Lesson 11: Crafting Stories with Data Project",
      "name": "Lesson 11: Crafting Stories with Data Project",
      "absolute_position": 12,
      "lockable": false,
      "has_lesson_plan": true,
      "relative_position": 11,
      "properties": {
        "assessment": true,
        "overview": "**What is the process of choosing a data set and forming a question to investigate?**\n\nOn Day 1, students will choose a dataset to investigate and generate RSAIR questions. They will familiarize themselves with their dataset through a Three Reads of Data, select a data question to investigate, and start discussing potential barriers to success.",
        "preparation": "* Provide a copy of the project guide for each student\n* **(Optional)** Print out a copy of the Data Question Peer Review for each student",
        "student_overview": "**What is the process of choosing a data set and forming a question to investigate?**\n\nToday, you will choose a dataset, go through a Three Reads of Data, and form your RSAIR data question. You will also discuss any potential barriers to completing the project."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "lesson.key": "Lesson 11: Crafting Stories with Data Project",
        "lesson_group.key": "lessonGroup-4",
        "script.name": "aif6-v2-2025"
      }
    },
